Walt Disney has launched its first multi-sport direct-to-consumer premium subscription streaming service – ESPN+. “ESPN+ delivers thousands of live sports events, exclusive original series, films and studio shows, plus unmatched an on-demand library,” said ESPN. The service is available in the ESPN App, it added. “As part of a subscription to ESPN+, fans will receive app and streaming experience enhancements,” it said. This includes: The ESPN app with ESPN+ is available on the Amazon Fire TV, Apple iPhone and iPads, Apple TV, Android smartphones, Android TV, and Chromecast.